ENTREZ_list <- bitr(
  geneID = rownames(DEG_list),
  fromType = "SYMBOL",
  toType = "ENTREZID",
  OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db
)
## 'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns
## Warning in bitr(geneID = rownames(DEG_list), fromType = "SYMBOL", toType =
## "ENTREZID", : 4.23% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
markers <-  ENTREZ_list %>% inner_join(markers, by = "SYMBOL")

# Removing genes that are not statistically significant. 
markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)
#head(markers, n = 50)

pos.markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC > 0) %>%  arrange(desc(abs(avg_log2FC)))
#head(pos.markers, n = 50)

pos.ranks <- pos.markers$ENTREZID[abs(pos.markers$avg_log2FC) > 0]
#head(pos.ranks)

pos_go <- enrichGO(gene = pos.ranks,           #a vector of entrez gene id
                   OrgDb = "org.Mm.eg.db",    
                   ont = "BP",
                   readable = TRUE)              #whether mapping gene ID to gene Name

ENTREZ_list <- bitr(
  geneID = rownames(DEG_list),
  fromType = "SYMBOL",
  toType = "ENTREZID",
  OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db
)
## 'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns
## Warning in bitr(geneID = rownames(DEG_list), fromType = "SYMBOL", toType =
## "ENTREZID", : 4.73% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
markers <-  ENTREZ_list %>% inner_join(markers, by = "SYMBOL")

# Removing genes that are not statistically significant. 
markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)
#head(markers, n = 50)

pos.markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC > 0) %>%  arrange(desc(abs(avg_log2FC)))
#head(pos.markers, n = 50)

pos.ranks <- pos.markers$ENTREZID[abs(pos.markers$avg_log2FC) > 0]
#head(pos.ranks)

pos_go <- enrichGO(gene = pos.ranks,           #a vector of entrez gene id
                   OrgDb = "org.Mm.eg.db",    
                   ont = "BP",
                   readable = TRUE)              #whether mapping gene ID to gene Name

pos_go

ENTREZ_list <- bitr(
  geneID = rownames(DEG_list),
  fromType = "SYMBOL",
  toType = "ENTREZID",
  OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db
)
## 'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns
## Warning in bitr(geneID = rownames(DEG_list), fromType = "SYMBOL", toType =
## "ENTREZID", : 28.72% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
markers <-  ENTREZ_list %>% inner_join(markers, by = "SYMBOL")

# Removing genes that are not statistically significant. 
markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)
#head(markers, n = 50)

pos.markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC > 0) %>%  arrange(desc(abs(avg_log2FC)))
#head(pos.markers, n = 50)

pos.ranks <- pos.markers$ENTREZID[abs(pos.markers$avg_log2FC) > 0]
#head(pos.ranks)

pos_go <- enrichGO(gene = pos.ranks,           #a vector of entrez gene id
                   OrgDb = "org.Mm.eg.db",    
                   ont = "BP",
                   readable = TRUE)              #whether mapping gene ID to gene Name

ENTREZ_list <- bitr(
  geneID = rownames(DEG_list),
  fromType = "SYMBOL",
  toType = "ENTREZID",
  OrgDb = org.Mm.eg.db
)
## 'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns
## Warning in bitr(geneID = rownames(DEG_list), fromType = "SYMBOL", toType =
## "ENTREZID", : 52.38% of input gene IDs are fail to map...
markers <-  ENTREZ_list %>% inner_join(markers, by = "SYMBOL")

# Removing genes that are not statistically significant. 
markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(p_val_adj < 0.05)
#head(markers, n = 50)

pos.markers <-  markers %>% dplyr::filter(avg_log2FC > 0) %>%  arrange(desc(abs(avg_log2FC)))
#head(pos.markers, n = 50)

pos.ranks <- pos.markers$ENTREZID[abs(pos.markers$avg_log2FC) > 0]
#head(pos.ranks)

pos_go <- enrichGO(gene = pos.ranks,           #a vector of entrez gene id
                   OrgDb = "org.Mm.eg.db",    
                   ont = "BP",
                   readable = TRUE)              #whether mapping gene ID to gene Name

pos_go
